{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SnapshotManager"},{"type":"text","text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the VM’s disk image ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"type":"text","text":") and auxiliary storage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"auxiliary.bin"},{"type":"text","text":"), stored in a named subdirectory under the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bundle’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SavedStates\/"},{"type":"text","text":" directory."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"How Snapshots Work","anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The VM "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must be stopped"}]},{"type":"text","text":" before saving or restoring."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the snapshot copies."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"APFS Copy-on-Write","anchor":"APFS-Copy-on-Write"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On APFS volumes, both save and restore use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileManager.copyItem"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which the system maps to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clonefile(2)"},{"type":"text","text":". This produces a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"copy-on-write clone instead of a byte-for-byte copy, making"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snapshot creation and restoration near-instantaneous regardless"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of disk image size. Only blocks that diverge after the clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consume additional storage."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Snapshot Directory Layout","anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Example","anchor":"Example"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","","\/\/ Save a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.save(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ List snapshots","let snapshots = try SnapshotManager.list(bundle: bundle)","for snap in snapshots {","    print(\"\\(snap.label): \\(snap.sizeInBytes) bytes\")","}","","\/\/ Restore a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.restore(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ Delete a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.delete(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","title":"SnapshotManager","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit15SnapshotManagerO","symbolKind":"enum","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotError"],"anchor":"Snapshots","title":"Snapshots"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/infoFileName","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/savedStatesDirectory"],"anchor":"Type-Properties","title":"Type Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/delete(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/list(bundle:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/restore(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/save(bundle:label:)"],"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages disk-level snapshots for virtual machine bundles."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotmanager"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotManager/resto